$comment: Actual temperature precision is 1F. The decimal part of the temperature controls the swing mode of the fan - X.0 is swing off, X.5 is swing on.

fan_only.$comment: Fan-only mode. No temperature control. Fan mode 'low' is lowest fan speed (F1), followed by 'medium' (F2), 'high' (F3), and 'max' (F4).

heat.$comment: Heat mode. No temperature control - heater is always on. Fan mode 'low' is lowest heat power (H1/650W), followed by 'medium' (H2/1000W) and 'high' (H3/1500W). Fan mode 'max' is full heat + low fan ('heater fan' mode/HF).

auto.$comment: 'Auto Eco' mode (heat with target temperature). No fan or heat power control in this mode.
